info: Imagine the number line broken into bins, each of size binSize, i.e. the first is from 0 to binSize-1, the second from binSize to 2binSize-1, etc.  (In this implementation, binSize equals 1000000.)  In the table we store the number of primes from bin 0 to i, 0<=i<binSize.  Then, to retrieve the nth prime, the program adds up the numbers until the sum exceeds n.  We then know exactly which bin the nth prime falls into.  The prime can then be found using a sieve algorithm on that bin. this table took approximately 15 minutes to be computed, with binSize equal to 1000000 and numberOfBins equal to 50000 we can get up to 2119654578 nth prime number
